						<div class="postbody">A table generator program just needs to write a file full of <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.byte</tt> statements that you <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.include</tt> in your main assembly file. An example of such a table generator for an exponential function is at <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_period_table" class="postlink">APU period table</a>. It should be straightforward to adapt it to a sine table.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
