					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you really want to do it without a lookup table, you could approximate the value using the Taylor series for sin/cos, calculated out to some degree of precision.<br /><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_series#Trigonometric_functions" class="postlink">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_series#Trigonometric_functions</a><br /><br />But then you'd need functions for division, exponentiation, and factorial all without lookup tables...<br />By the time you coded that all up, it would likely use more ROM than just having the original, single lookup table.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://zutanogames.com/" class="postlink">http://zutanogames.com/</a> &lt;-- my dev blog</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

